    body: "St. Maria Goretti (1890-1902) was an Italian peasant girl who was stabbed fourteen times by her neighbor, Alessandro Serenelli, when she resisted his attempt to rape her. As she lay dying, she forgave her attacker, saying she wanted him to be in heaven with her. She died the next day. Alessandro was imprisoned for thirty years, during which he experienced a vision of Maria offering him flowers. He converted, did penance, and was present in St. Peter's Square when Maria was canonized in 1950.",
