    body: "St. Monica (c. 331-387) was a Christian woman from North Africa who endured a difficult marriage to a pagan husband and the heartbreak of watching her brilliant son Augustine embrace heresy and immorality. For nearly two decades she followed him, prayed for him, and wept for his conversion. A bishop reassured her: 'It is not possible that the son of so many tears should perish.' Her prayers were answered when Augustine was baptized by St. Ambrose in Milan in 387. She died shortly after, at peace.",
    example: "Monica followed Augustine from Carthage to Rome to Milan, never ceasing to pray and fast for his conversion. When he was finally baptized at the Easter Vigil of 387, she said, 'There is nothing more I want in this life. My hopes on earth are now fulfilled.'",
